1. In github create a repo
2. clone the repo in local system with the command 
    - git clone https_git_url.git
3. Add the files in the folder
4. Stage the files 
    Stage single file Command: git add 05_dictionary\dic.py
    Stage all files command: git add .
5. commit with a message
    - git commit -m "python tutorial files added"
6. push the code
    git push origin branch_name[main]

7. Pull code from github
    git pull origin main

8. check current git branch
    git branch
